relevant_findings.general: Generally well appearing, in no acute distress, markedly jaundiced.
relevant_findings.HEENT: PERRLA. Oropharynx clear with moist mucous membranes. No gum hypertrophy. +scleral icterus.
relevant_findings.lymph: No palpable cervical or supraclavicular lymphadenopathy.
relevant_findings.CV: Regular rate and rhythm, S1, S2, systolic murmur at unspecified position.
relevant_findings.abdomen: Soft, non-distended, positive bowel sounds. Diffusely tender to palpation, most prominent in epigastric region. Negative for rebound or guarding.
relevant_findings.neuro: Alert and oriented. Grossly normal strength, coordination, and gait.
relevant_findings.lines: Left PIV without erythema or tenderness.
